ackground-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-va=
riant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space=
: pre-wrap;"><strong>Percentage Error =3D 8 =E2=80=93 10/10 x 100 =3D -2/10=
 x 100 =3D -20%.</strong>&nbsp;</span></p>
<h1 dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 10pt; margin-bottom:=
 0pt;"><span style=3D"font-size: 16pt; font-family: Cambria, serif; color: =
#000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: norm=
al; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; =
white-space: pre-wrap;">What are the Differences between Percentage Error, =
Absolute Error, and Relative Error?<br>
</span></h1>
<p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 1=
0pt;"><span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; b=
ackground-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-va=
riant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space=
: pre-wrap;">The absolute error is simply the absolute value (written as |x=
|) between the experimental measure and the actual measure (the difference =
between the two, ignoring any negative sign). It provides a magnitude of th=
e difference between both figures.** In comparison, the relative error refe=
rs to the ratio between the absolute error and the actual value. You can ca=
lculate it by dividing the absolute error and the actual value. For instanc=
e, if the absolute error is 2 and the actual value is 6, the relative error=
 is 2/6, which is 0.3333=E2=80=A6 When the relative error is turned into a =
percentage, it becomes a percentage error.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 1=
0pt;"><span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; b=
ackground-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-va=
riant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space=
: pre-wrap;">In summary</span><span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: =
Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; fo=
nt-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-ali=
gn: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">:&nbsp;</span></p>
